  "texts": [
    "It is considered a controllable summarization method because it produces summaries based on user input, which can specify entities of interest (in the form of keywords), summary length, and questions that the summary should answer.",
    "The system is a fine-tuned version of the BART LARGE model (Lewis et al., 2020) based on three training datasets: CNN/DM, arXiv scientific papers (Cohan et al., 2018), and BIGPATENT (patent documents, Sharma et al. 2019).",
    "Sum is designed to separate test-time user control of summarization and the training process.",
    "During training, summaries are conditioned on the source document and automatically extracted keywords.",
    "At test time, a control function is applied to map control aspects to keywords, while model parameters from training remain unchanged."
